<p><strong>« <a href="/news-06-2019">June 2019</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-07-2019">July 2019</a></span> | <a href="/news-08-2019">August 2019</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The <strong><a href="/collaboration-contest">Collaboration Contest</a></strong> that started the previous month has ended. Congratulations to the winners! Be sure to check out all the entries on the contest page.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The Seminars and Workshops initiative has had an active month. Seminars on providing quick crit and finding and using CC-compliant images were carried out over IRC. Check the <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10752847/seminars-and-workshops#post-4193637">Seminars and Workshops</a></strong> post for schedule of upcoming events.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2886">SCP-2886</a> (&quot;Planet-Hopping Volcano&quot;) - <em>Since it was discovered on Triton, SCP-2886 has teleported 10 times.</em> Written by Multiscoop</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3052">SCP-3052</a> (&quot;Disturbed&quot;) - <em>However, it was discovered that any subject viewing SCP-3052-1 will perceive it as facing them directly, no matter which angle or direction the subject views it from.</em> Written by Witryso</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/being-cactusman">Being Cactusman</a> - <em>What few scientists bother to worry about is whether or not plants dream. They do.</em> Written by Riemann</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/lte-2712-bosch">LTE-2712-Bosch</a> - <em>A series of teeth (40 confirmed instances) which appeared spontaneously in and above the Arctic Ocean on 04/08/2███.</em> Written by shaggydredlocks</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-1169">SCP-1169</a> (&quot;Lamarck's Giraffe&quot;) - <em>Assignment preference will be given to staff who are irreversibly infertile.</em> Written by wishun, selected by <em>wishun</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3844">SCP-3844</a> (&quot;To Slay A Dragon&quot;) - <em>A dragon. There was a dragon in the mountains. And it looked just like we'd imagined.</em> Written by Captain Kirby, selected by <em>DrSevere</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3881">SCP-3881</a> (&quot;A Disregarded Proposal&quot;) - <em>When worn by a human being, SCP-3881 will immediately transport the wearer to an unknown location.</em> Written by Ayers, selected by <em>RockTeethMothEyes</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/you-never-visit-anymore">You Never Visit Me Anymore</a> - <em>She pushed page after page into my hands, always littered with notes and lines under words, in red Sharpie.</em> Written by Zachary Maxwell, selected by <em>Zachary Maxwell</em></li>
</ul>
